pieces.title: Gymnopedie No. 1
pieces.description: Elegant and slightly dark, the simplicity of the piano melody is light and touching, with a feeling of pensive restraint. It is beautiful accompaniment to the close of a drama, or of a midday reverie. Composed by Erik Satie.

pieces.title: Gymnopedie No. 2
pieces.description: This piece is dramatic and very dynamic; in the beginning and towards the end the music is soft and tender, but it is punctuated by aggressive changes in volume and minor chords throughout. This piece could work well to depict grief, as the emotions and feelings are similarly mercurial. Composed by Erik Satie.

pieces.title: At The Shore
pieces.description: A mixture of African vocal chants and Caribbean-styled percussion and bass guitar makes you long for your hammock. The piece is relaxing and gets you in the mood for ?Island Time? - where the troubles of the world melt away in the ocean breeze.

pieces.title: Fluffing a Duck
pieces.instruments: Tuba, Flute, Trombones, Bass Clarinet, Clarinet, Percussion
pieces.description: A trombone plays a humorous melody alongside timpanis and a variety of woodwind instruments. This music is suited for a short theme for a comedic piece that relies on visual jokes.  2 Small versions in one file.

pieces.title: The Forest and the Trees
pieces.description: A peaceful exploration of the interplay between woodwinds weaving through a melody, underscored by soft brass chords. The music evokes scenes of nature, acceptance, and quietude.

pieces.title: Autumn Day
pieces.instruments: Guitar, Bass, Kit, Strings, Piano, Choir
pieces.description: A reflective piece with piano, guitar, simplified percussion, and subtle strings, this music is calm and comforting, like a good book and a hot cup of tea. The chord progressions are interesting and repeat often, which gives the piece a memorable quality.

pieces.title: Itty Bitty 8 Bit
pieces.description: Playful and interesting, Itty Bitty 8-Bit immediately introduces you to a pulsating melody flitting above a synthesized bass. The melody changes in the second minute and builds while climbing the chromatic scale, before settling back into the familiar refrain. This could be looped for a classic-styled videogame that is quirky and imaginative.

pieces.title: Windswept
pieces.description: A relaxed guitar and strings piece for the denouement of a story or exposition of the scenic outdoors. The guitar is peaceful as the strings gently build in prominence. The tempo is regular overall, but slows down in key moments to build a sense of tranquility.

pieces.title: Honey Bee
pieces.description: The electric piano alternates between playing the rhythm and creating a sliding melody, while trumpets sound in the background, sometimes stealing the melody. The percussion makes for a toe-tapping good time. This is useful for the closing segment of a TV show, game, or transition. Cleanly loopable.

pieces.title: There It Is
pieces.description: Very quick and jovial, this brass heavy piece has a guitar riff that sticks in the brain, but ends suddenly. Useful for a quick theme introduction, transition, or for a fast and exciting commercial.

pieces.title: Show Your Moves
pieces.description:
Your toe will start tapping to the bump of the bass drum once the music pans through your speakers. This song is one for a successful accomplishment or the happy ending to a difficult challenge. The staccato melody resembles a synthesized tremolo violin, while the bass guitar thumps increase in prominence until they are your heartbeat.
This piece of music is available in an uncompressed format here.

pieces.title: At Rest
pieces.description: A recurring voice melody cascades over piano chords that sway in the breeze. Strings and horns then play the melody as the piano is slightly more forceful before settling again. It is suggestive of sadness, but with a sense of closure and peace.

pieces.title: Procession of the King
pieces.description: A strings only piece, evocative of love, romance, and pride. Just before the one minute mark the music takes an unexpected turn, becoming intensely emotional and beautiful as the strings play in the higher register with a slight tremolo, with the bass filling up the empty space in the last half minute.

pieces.title: Cattails
pieces.description: An acoustic guitar and a banjo create a drifting lull as an accordion and erhu play a languid melody. The accordion is slightly forceful, while the tremolo of the erhu is uncertain, creating an intertwined dialogue of two vastly different characters. The piece is calm and pensive, with subtle notes of East Asian and Country Western influences.

pieces.title: Pinball Spring 160
pieces.description: Triumphant and exuberant, this arcade groove is bright and perfect for retro games or humorous video content. Super fast J-Pop feel version.

pieces.title: Pinball Spring
pieces.description: Triumphant and exuberant, this arcade groove is bright and perfect for retro games or humorous video content. It has a thumping beat that is light-hearted, and is easily looped for continuous play.

pieces.title: Tafi Maradi no voice
pieces.description:
Percussion beats and shakers instantly make your feet tap, involving you in the tribal experience of ritual kinship. Three sets of call-and-response chanting slide into the forefront of the beat, interspersed with rapid djembe solos to the ending when the dust finally settles.
This piece of music is available in an uncompressed format here.

pieces.title: Merry Go - Distressed
pieces.description: Comedic and playful, this rag-time ditty has a strong melody, and is heavy in the bass chords. The second minute features flighty finger-work, as if an energetic bee is flying up and down the scales. The last thirty seconds is a refrain of the introduction, and the piece ends with an invigorating flourish.

pieces.description: Comedic and playful, this rag-time ditty has a strong melody, and is heavy in the bass chords. The last thirty seconds is a refrain of the introduction, and the piece ends with an invigorating flourish.

pieces.description: Comedic and playful, this rag-time ditty has a strong melody, and is heavy in the bass chords. The second minute features flighty finger-work, as if an energetic bee is flying up and down the scales. The last thirty seconds is a refrain of the introduction, and the piece ends with an invigorating flourish.

pieces.title: Court of the Queen
pieces.description: Slow Waltz. English Waltz. Foxtrot. Slow Fox. Regal in its construction, this waltz is meant for the ballroom floor of a grand soiree. The pizzicato strings provide the rhythm in the first half, while strings and horns play the melody. A harp accompanies a celeste in creating transitions between segments of the music. As the music crescendos into the third minute, the frivolity turns more serious, and the piece ends with a few interchangeable chords between the celeste and the horns.

pieces.title: Rains Will Fall
pieces.description: Slow Waltz. English Waltz. Foxtrot. Slow Fox. The piano plays a mournful, waltzing melody, while strings enter gently. Halfway into the second minute, the tone is more hopeful, but then returns to the sadness of the introduction.  Just before the third minute ends the hope returns, but melts again into sadness with the final high note of the piano. This is music for a rainy day, or when the hero to a story has lost his way.

pieces.title: Spazzmatica Polka
pieces.description: Boisterous and nearly obnoxious, this piece will lodge itself in your brain and make you think you?re trapped in an arcade. The polka rhythm is quick and the melody is spastic. Right into the second minute the rhythm drops out and introduces a crazed, comedic melody that continues throughout until the abrupt end.

pieces.title: Thatched Villagers
pieces.description: Solid in pace, The Thatched Roof Villagers moves with percussion and a number of flutes and pipes struggling for dominance. The real joy of the piece is halfway through when the tinny dulcimer plays the melody and is then joined by the flutes in melody and harmony. The music is jovial and inviting. Loopable.

pieces.title: Eastminster
pieces.description: The constant reverberating sound of rain and the perfect-fifth drone of the strings are calming, but have an air of suspense and tension about them, as if a drama is about to unfold. The koto plays a near continuous refrain, at times forcefully. Evoking pre-colonialist East Asia, the piece is beautiful and stoic in tone, especially as the koto asserts its dominance in the sixth minute and at the end.

pieces.title: Silver Blue Light
pieces.description: Sparse in it?s instrumentation, Silver Blue Light is quiet and pensive with atmospheric synthesized chords and guitar.. There isn?t much of a melodic line to this piece until well into the fifth minute. In the third minute the guitar plays a few high notes, and the key changes briefly, which occurs again in the final twenty seconds as well.

pieces.title: Porch Swing Days - faster
pieces.description: Acoustic guitars play a constantly flowing feel-good melody, enhanced by an airy chorus that enters early in the piece. The music is bright and evokes a carefree attitude towards life and the troubles of the world.

pieces.title: Porch Swing Days - slower
pieces.description: Acoustic guitars play a constantly flowing feel-good melody, enhanced by an airy chorus that enters early in the piece. The music is bright and evokes a carefree attitude towards life and the troubles of the world.

pieces.title: Sweeter Vermouth
pieces.instruments: Tenor Sax, Alto Sax, Trumpets, Vibes, Trombones, Kit
pieces.description: The jaunty bass line keeps this short piece moving at a solid pace, while the vibraphone and saxophones play the swinging melody, until the bright, thump of an ending. Use this piece as a slick transition between scenes or for the background to a short scene of drinking, gambling, or dancing.

pieces.title: Finding the Balance
pieces.description: The beginning is calm with the Middle Eastern dudek playing the melody. As the electronic elements melt into the dudek and the plucked strings, the groove is established.  Just into the third minute the melody changes to beautiful and touching, but returns to the feel of the intro, while a woman?s voice sings a haunting melody in a distant language. This is music of wonder, and is best as exposition music for a film about nature or a group of people struggling to survive.

pieces.title: Fig Leaf Rag - distressed
pieces.description: The classic ragtime ditty of Scott Joplin, perfect for a silent film of whimsy and humor. The piece begins with a short intro, then plays the bouncy rhythm of with a bright plodding beat. At the end of the third minute, the pace quickens, and leads into a darker refrain, but the jolly melody returns for the finale.  With added record player effects.

pieces.title: Fig Leaf Rag
pieces.description: The classic ragtime ditty of Scott Joplin, perfect for a silent film of whimsy and humor. The piece begins with a short intro, then plays the bouncy rhythm of with a bright plodding beat. At the end of the third minute, the pace quickens, and leads into a darker refrain, but the jolly melody returns for the finale.

pieces.title: For Originz
pieces.description: Heavy strings play several chords before a violin enters with a sliding melody, in tandem with a woman?s voice and flute. The bass drums are barely perceptible, but accentuate the orchestra as the three melodic personalities float amongst the music. The music is full of wonder and power, and ends in a strong chord, evoking a connection with nature.

pieces.title: Open Those Bright Eyes
pieces.description: This piece is made up of three distinct variations on a melodic theme, and should be taken apart and used for transitions in a light-hearted short video. The first section begins with a bright, leading to the big push of the bombastic brass. The second section, beginning at 0:52, is the same melody, but only features the piano. This section is softer and lasts 20 seconds. The final section begins at 1:17, and ends with an excited flourish.

pieces.title: Finding Movement
pieces.description: The koto in this piece follows a steady, plodding beat, while the orchestral strings provide a drone-like background. At 0:33 the strings crescendo to follow the melody of the koto, but at 1:18 the tempo slows and the strings fade away, only to return to highlight the final chord.  With the even rhythm and the sharply accentuated plucks of the koto, this is best used as an introduction to a short film or game, or the resolution to a conflict surrounding family or challenges to tradition.

pieces.title: Ripples
pieces.description: Flowing like water, this serene piece is perfect for relaxation and meditation. pieces.title: Meditation Impromptu 03
pieces.description: A single piano impromptu in D flat Major, broken into three files for easier downloading. There is nothing startling contained in this piece... only light flowing melodies.

pieces.title: Midday Dance

pieces.title: Midsummer Sky

The bass in this piece is actually a sample from an 18th century double bass. Most latin players aren't likely to be on one of these... but it was the only one I had at the time.

pieces.title: Modern Vibes
pieces.description: Modern Vibraphone composition. 4 mallet, plays with rhythm over the entire range of the instrument.

pieces.title: Moonstone

pieces.title: Night on the Docks - Trumpet
pieces.description: Sad and smooth; Think 1950's detective film.

pieces.title: Night on the Docks - Piano
pieces.description: Sad and smooth; Think 1950's detective film.

pieces.description: Basic Salsa.

pieces.description: Basic Salsa.

pieces.title: Numinous Shine

pieces.instruments: Kit, Bass, Piano, Trumpet, Tenor Sax, Vibe

pieces.title: Thaxted (Holst)

pieces.title: The Chase
pieces.description: Light and fast. For... well - chase sequences.

pieces.title: There is Romance
pieces.description: Slow and poignant, this piece is excellent for depicting childhood love, the swelling love of adolescence, or the tender caresses of old age. The simple, elegant melody is exceptionally suitable to weddings, faith services, or as a theme to a story of lasting love.

pieces.title: Touching Moments Five - Circle
pieces.description: A simple tour through every major key in order. Arpeggiated with some connecting melodic notes.

pieces.title: Touching Moments Four - Melody
pieces.description: More melodic than most of the pieces presented here - can be distracting, or can be just what you're looking for. Famous from the Sad Fairy Dress-up game.

pieces.title: Touching Moments One - Pulse
pieces.description: Open and airy. A classic "touching moment" style. Performance imperfections are exaggerated to give a more "choked up" feel.

pieces.title: Touching Moments Two - Higher
pieces.description: Only notes from the very highest registers of the piano are used in this. It can cut through ambient noise and still provide a presence.

pieces.title: Touching Story
pieces.description: Very very slow and changeable.

pieces.title: Transition One
pieces.instruments: Orchestral - Flute, Clarinet, Bass Clarinet, Bass, Cello, Viola, Violin, Glock, Harp

pieces.title: Trio for Piano, Cello, and Clarinet
pieces.filename: Trio for Piano, Cello, and Clarinet.mp3
pieces.description: More contemplative than outright depressing. Tempo is highly variable, so don't count on it if you have to synch to something. I didn't know there was a tradition of writing for this instrumentation. It works very well.

pieces.title: Two Together
pieces.description: Sparkly open voicings.
